{
  "_comment": [
    "==========================================================================",
    "QUALYS → MANAGE ENGINE  |  routing_rules.json",
    "==========================================================================",
    "SETUP INSTRUCTIONS (do this once per customer):",
    "",
    "  STEP 1 — Fill in 'picklist_reference' below.",
    "           Log into ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus and copy the EXACT picklist",
    "           values for each field into the lists. These are your reference.",
    "",
    "  STEP 2 — Fill in 'defaults' using values from your picklist_reference.",
    "           These apply to ALL tickets when no rule matches.",
    "",
    "  STEP 3 — Fill in 'severity_map' using values from your picklist_reference.",
    "           This maps Qualys severity (Critical/High/Medium/Low/Very Low)",
    "           to ME fields like Priority, Urgency, Impact.",
    "",
    "  STEP 4 — Fill in 'rules' to route specific vulnerability types.",
    "           Each rule matches keywords from the Qualys data and overrides",
    "           specific ticket fields (e.g. Category, Group) for that vuln type.",
    "",
    "  IMPORTANT: Leave any field as empty string \"\" to skip it.",
    "             The script will NOT send empty fields to ME.",
    "             Even if a wrong value is sent, the script catches the error,",
    "             drops that field, and still creates the ticket. No ticket is lost.",
    "=========================================================================="
  ],
